   <concept id="FAR_9_405_1" class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">9.405-1</ph> Continuation of current
contracts.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d583e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d610e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Contractors debarred, suspended, <ph rev="FAC 2025-03 January 17, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-015?>proposed for debarment, or voluntarily excluded<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 9.405-1 by—   a. Removing from paragraph (a) heading “ or proposed for debarment  ” and adding “  proposed for debarment, or voluntarily excluded  ” in its place;?></ph>
                  </i>.</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d610e18">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Notwithstanding the debarment, suspension, <ph rev="FAC 2025-03 January 17, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-015?>proposed debarment, or voluntary exclusion, of<?FM MARKER [Why] b. Removing from paragraph (a)(1) “or proposed debarment of” and “or proposed for debarment unless” and adding “proposed debarment, or voluntary exclusion, of” and “proposed for debarment, or voluntarily excluded, unless” in their places, respectively; and?></ph> a contractor, agencies may continue contracts or subcontracts in existence at the time the contractor was debarred, suspended, <ph rev="FAC 2025-03 January 17, 2025" class="- topic/ph ">proposed for debarment, or voluntarily excluded, unless</ph> the agency head directs otherwise. A decision as to the type of termination action, if any, to be taken should be made only after review by agency contracting and technical personnel and by counsel to ensure the propriety of the proposed action.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d610e23">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> For contractors debarred, suspended, <ph rev="FAC 2025-03 January 17, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2019-015?>proposed for debarment, or voluntarily excluded, unless<?FM MARKER [Why] c. Removing from paragraph (a)(2) introductory text “or proposed for debarment, unless” and adding “proposed for debarment, or voluntarily excluded, unless” in its place.?></ph> the agency head makes a written determination of the compelling reasons for doing so, ordering activities shall not—</p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d610e29">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Place orders exceeding the guaranteed
minimum under indefinite quantity contracts;</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d610e34">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Place orders
under Federal Supply Schedule contracts, blanket purchase agreements,
or basic ordering agreements; or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d610e39">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(iii)</ph> Add new
work, exercise options, or otherwise extend the duration of current
contracts or orders.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d610e44">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> Ineligible
contractors. A covered agency, as defined in <xref href="9.110-1.dita#FAR_9_110_1"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">9.110-1</xref>,
shall terminate existing contracts and shall not place new orders
or award new contracts with contractors that have been declared
ineligible pursuant to <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section983&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html"
                        class="- topic/xref ">10 U.S.C. 983</xref> (see <xref href="9.110.dita#FAR_9_110"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">9.110</xref>),
except for contracts at or below the simplified acquisition threshold
or contracts for the acquisition of commercial products and
commercial services.
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
